{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bb92b91d-c700-46e7-8118-42dc8a4abdf2","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Change base images\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n```bash\ndotnet restore   # pull updated packages\ndotnet build     # verify it compiles\ndotnet test      # run tests\n```\n\nAlso review your NuGet packages — any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` references should be updated to their 11.x versions. Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/migration/) for any breaking changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"819fbcd3-c3be-4113-9389-0849d7ee8a57","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":328,"requestId":"B41D:180EFF:8E357A:B024C6:6A0135D2"},"id":"cb42357c-8460-44da-af74-214836f2d2a7","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:50:17.725Z","parentId":"6d97c14a-5664-42d7-94f4-16ce61fe2410"}
